<br>
So, for argument's sake, say it was done a year ago.  It was a big deal to those guilds who were competing very hard for the few remaining Velious server-wide firsts (with NToV first being cleared by FoH around the last week of June / first week of July).  The warders and sleepers saw several retunings in the Spring of 2001 as VI had a nasty time finally finishing the script post-SoV release.<br>
<br>
If you want to split hairs, the sleeper was awoken a couple times before that while VI tried to fix the broken zone.  The famous 50' tall naked human model was awoken, multiple versions of the model were awoken, the disaster surrounding Conquest, all kinds of buggy stuff, but the first sleeper awakening of the final version of the zone belongs to BotS.<br>
<br>
On a side note, all the mobs in Sleepers are on their third or fourth faction set.<br>
<br>
Once it was done, it was assumed Sleepers itself would be changed in such a was as to now recaputre the Sleeper in some way.  However, the quest couldn't be found, although the ultra rare Prysmatic Dragon Scale appeared as a random drop.  A few more guilds awoke the sleeper in hopes they would be the first to find the quest and earn the prestiege of being the first to figure it out.<br>
<br>
The quest does not exist.......so people soon realized.<br>
People kept looking and looking and looking.....<br>
People bitched and bitched and bitched....<br>
VI eventually said, Waking the Sleeper is working as intended.<br>
So, there is no quest, no means of killing Kerafrym, will never be any means of killing or recapturing him.  Accpet it.<br>
<br>
Basically, waking the sleeper is now exposed to be the premiere selfish act of EQ.  You screw the rest of the server for a few minutes of deathtouches and a couple of cool screen shots.  A few very nice items will be completely eliminated from the server and outfitting your guild in primal, while still possible, becomes a big pain in the ass.<br>
<br>
FnF will make their chioce, and probabaly doesn't give a shit about my opinion.  But, I hope they do so knowing all the facts.<br>
<br>
The real paranoia is....eventually you want to kill the fourth warder for his stuff and the nice challenge he presents (unresistable 70% AE slow....).  When you do that, you have to leave one of the other 4 warders up, or else the sleeper wakes up.  By this time, people won't really want items off the first warder, but if you know what you're doing, he can be killed with like 15 or 16 people.  So, people worry that some other guild will sneak in and wake him up.  Don't laugh, it happened on one of the PVP servers.  But, I have a lot of faith that people get along much, much better here.<br>
<br>
Chysl<br>
<br>
P.S.  I think you can add Karana to the list of servers that never woke him up.  Their guids just agreed not to do it, it's as simple as that.<br>
