<br>
In most games, with most high-level, nigh-invincible mobs, you can go back and adjust your tactics, correct for error and what went wrong the last time. Each attempt gets a little closer, sometimes steps backwards a bit, but all in all brings us a lot closer to taking out the baddy. This can be done because these targets don't despawn. They can be attempted time and again. Screw up the last Nagafen raid, try again, maybe you'll get it right this time. The Sleeper is not like this. From all I hear, he despawns and you only get one shot. After that if you still want to take him, it's on to the next server and hope they don't wake him before you're good enough there. <br>
